BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pt 2: Glaze as a Completion of Form with Ping Zhong — Sebastopol
  Center For the Arts\, California
DTSTART:20260418T000000
DTEND:20260419T000000
UID:142952735a64cee5d77faa4e9354bc36@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Pt 2: Glaze as a Completion of Form with Ping Zhong\n\n  \n   
  \n      \n        \n          $10.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nSatur
 day\, April 18\, 2026\; 10am-11amLocated in the Ceramics StudioThis sessio
 n will explore how glaze can enhance and finalize a piece. SebArts’ Cera
 mics Residency Artist\, Ping Zhong\, plans to spend the first month testin
 g the studio’s existing glazes to understand their behavior\, and will a
 lso bring a few personal glaze recipes to share\, along with fired samples
 . Application methods and techniques for achieving specific effects will b
 e demonstrated. The instructor will have works ready for glazing\, and par
 ticipants from the previous workshop may also have pieces they wish to gla
 ze.Due to limited capacity of the Ceramics Studio\, we are asking for a su
 ggested donation of $10 to confirm your attendance. About the Artist: Ping
  Zhong’s artistic practice is a continuous exploration of regeneration
 —of materials\, forms\, and cultural narratives. She investigates the di
 alogue between ancient Chinese pottery and contemporary visual language\, 
 using wheel-throwing\, hand-building\, and sculpture to create works in wh
 ich history and personal growth converge. This reinterpretation of classic
 al forms is not only an artistic method\, but also a philosophical inquiry
  into the harmony between past and future. Deeply motivated to uncover the
  potential within clay\, Ping pushes the boundaries of design and techniqu
 e. Her work reflects on universal themes: the individual’s place within 
 the community\, the relationship between essence and appearance\, and the 
 evolving connection between nature and society. Through these explorations
 \, she seeks to create art that resonates across cultures.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n            
 \n              \n                Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/pt-2-glaze-as-a-completion-of
 -form-with-ping-zhong
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Paper Lanterns Workshop — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, Calif
 ornia
DTSTART:20260419T000000
DTEND:20260420T000000
UID:0b2ea899ef80f7885f9155ba075c8bb1@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Out of Stock\n      \n    \n\n\n\n\nPaper Lanterns Workshop\n\
 n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $70.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \
 n\nSunday\, April 19\, 2026\; 1:00PM – 4:00PM$60 + $10 Materials feeDisc
 over the magic of paper cutting In this one-day workshop making your own p
 aper lantern.  Participants will learn paper cutting design and knife tec
 hnique\, and create a unique\, illuminated piece of art. After exploring 
 examples of paper cutting artists and their work\, students will dream up 
 their own paper lantern designs to execute with guidance and instruction. 
 Learn how to translate your ideas into a cut paper composition\, then how 
 to cut out your composition with minimized frustration. Finally\, we will 
 assemble our lanterns and illuminate them to bask in the glow of your effo
 rts. This class will cover: proper knife handling\, foundational paper cu
 tting skills\, and the basics of paper cutting design. A light box will be
  available if students would like to bring reference images to trace onto 
 their lantern materials. This class is suitable for artists of all skill 
 levels. All materials included\, including an electric votive to illuminat
 e your paper lantern safely. Safety Note: Participants must have strong en
 ough fine motor abilities to handle a sharp blade safely. About the Instr
 uctor: Hannah Day received her BA in Visual Arts with an emphasis on drawi
 ng and printmaking from University of San Diego\, then attended University
  of Hawaii at Manoa to receive her MFA in printmaking. Hannah’s etchings
  have been internationally shown and collected\, but her personal practice
  also includes paper cutting\, graphite\, watercolor\, mixed media\, and m
 urals. She has taught all ages and many formats (kids\, teens\, adults\, c
 ollege\, private lessons\, camps\, etc) and many mediums. These days\, Han
 nah has primarily been teaching watercolor classes\, but also teaches draw
 ing\, paper cutting\, and pop-up art. You can view her work at www.hannahd
 rawstrees.com\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n            \n              \n       
          Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/paper-lanterns-workshop
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
