SUMMARY:Pt. 3: Finding One’s Voice Through Art – A Second Life in Cera
 mics with Ping Zhong — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, California
DTSTART:20260502T000000
DTEND:20260503T000000
UID:81832a52f7f272fc5bd0f2c33221974a@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Pt. 3: Finding One’s Voice Through Art – A Second Life in 
 Ceramics with Ping Zhong\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $10.00\n
         \n      \n    \n  \n\nSaturday\, May 2\, 2026\; 2-3pmLocated in th
 e Fireside RoomSebArts’ Ceramics Residency Artist\, Ping Zhong\, will sh
 are their personal journey of discovering artistic expression through cera
 mics later in life\, introducing their work and experiences to illustrate 
 how art can become a meaningful path of self-discovery.Due to limited capa
 city of the Ceramics Studio\, we are asking for a suggested donation of $1
 0 to confirm your attendance. About the Artist: Ping Zhong’s artistic pr
 actice is a continuous exploration of regeneration—of materials\, forms\
 , and cultural narratives. She investigates the dialogue between ancient C
 hinese pottery and contemporary visual language\, using wheel-throwing\, h
 and-building\, and sculpture to create works in which history and personal
  growth converge. This reinterpretation of classical forms is not only an 
 artistic method\, but also a philosophical inquiry into the harmony betwee
 n past and future. Deeply motivated to uncover the potential within clay\,
  Ping pushes the boundaries of design and technique. Her work reflects on 
 universal themes: the individual’s place within the community\, the rela
 tionship between essence and appearance\, and the evolving connection betw
 een nature and society. Through these explorations\, she seeks to create a
 rt that resonates across cultures.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n            \n              \n      
