SUMMARY:Abstract Collage Minis - Create A Series — Sebastopol Center For
  the Arts\, California
DTSTART:20260517T000000
DTEND:20260518T000000
UID:c1a88ab7a62595336635fd6a8e8cc5b1@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Abstract Collage Minis - Create A Series\, 5/17\n\n  \n    \n 
      \n        \n          $130.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nSunday\,
  May 17\, 2026\; 11 AM - 3 PMFee: $115 + $15 materials feeAge: 16+ In this
  new workshop\, French-American collage artist Catherine Cruz will teach y
 ou how to create a dynamic series of abstract collages using elements such
  as color\, line and shape.  You will work on four small wood panels to co
 mpose a cohesive series. Working on several panels at once offers several 
 advantages\, including greater creative momentum\, the ability to build a 
 strong thematic connection between pieces\, and a way to maintain creative
  flow.  This technique allows for a deeper exploration of an idea or theme
  than is possible with a single piece. We will start with short compositio
 n exercises to discuss design principles and abstraction.  Then Catherine 
 will demonstrate her method for mounting papers on the panels.  You will h
 ave ample time to select papers and create your designs. What you’ll lea
 rn from this workshop: Reliable method for layering collage papers\, Creat
 ive ways to explore abstraction\, Techniques for creating a cohesive serie
 s\, Strategies for refining your compositionIMPORTANT: Instructions for wh
 ere to purchase your materials and how to prepare them is provided in the 
 attached PDF. We will take a short break for lunch between 12:30 and 1:00 
 pm so please bring your lunch and a beverage.   About the instructor: Cath
 erine Cruz is a French-American artist whose work is informed by textures 
 and patterns created by the passing of time and the effects of the natural
  elements on the built environment.  She holds a Bachelor of Science in in
 terior design and she worked in the field of architectural design and gree
 n building certification for over 25 years.  She has taught collage and mi
 xed media workshops in the Bay Area and in France since 2019\, and this is
  her fifth year at the Sebastopol Center for the Arts.  Her studio is loca
 ted in Sebastopol and she participates in Art Trails Open Studios.  You ma
 y contact Catherine at beyouartstudio@gmail.com.  Check out Catherine’s 
 other classes here:  https://wwws.sebarts.org/visual-arts-classes. \n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n   
